                        <pre class="page"><code>Add-Type -AssemblyName System.Drawing$imagesToDelete = Get-ChildItem . |Where-Object {try {$pic = [System.Drawing.Image]::FromFile($_.FullName)# We only want images that are / are not 800x600$pic.Width -eq 800$pic.Height -eq 600 # $pic.Width -ne 800# $pic.Height -ne 600 }catch{# Ignore errors (== probably not an image)}finally {# Clean upif($pic -is [IDisposable]){$pic.Dispose()}}}$imagesToDelete | Remove-Item </code></pre>
                      </li>
                    </ol>
                  </details>
                </li>
                <li>
                  <details>
                    <summary>
                      Parsing local \ remote html with PowerShell 5.1 match regex.
                    </summary>
                    <ol>
                      <li>Output everything between the body tags. Do not include / include &lt;body&gt; tags in results. See working on a local / remote file below. See find anything between any &lt;tag&gt; and the very first instance of &lt;/tag&gt; below.
                        <p><a href="https://javascript.info/regexp-greedy-and-lazy" rel="nofollow noreferrer">Greedy and lazy quantifiers explained</a></p>
                        <p><a href="https://regex101.com" rel="nofollow noreferrer">regex101.com</a> is your friend</p>
                      </li>
                      <li>
                        <p>Copy and paste into PowerShell 5.1. It will output everything between &lt;body&gt;&lt;/body&gt;. The results outputs twice. Once without the body tags and once with.</p>
                        <ol>
                          <li>
                            <pre class="page"><code>$testhtml = @'&lt;!doctype html&gt;&lt;html lang="en"&gt;&lt;head&gt;&lt;meta charset="utf-8"&gt;&lt;title&gt;AdminWeb&lt;/title&gt;&lt;base href="/wwwroot/admin-web/"&gt;&lt;meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1"&gt;&lt;link rel="icon" type="image/x-icon" href="favicon.ico"&gt;&lt;/head&gt;&lt;body&gt;&lt;app-root&gt;&lt;/app-root&gt;&lt;script src="/wwwroot/admin-web/runtime.js"&gt;&lt;/script&gt;&lt;script src="/wwwroot/admin-web/file1.js" nomodule&gt;&lt;/script&gt;&lt;script src="/wwwroot/admin-web/file2.js"&gt;&lt;/script&gt;&lt;script src="/wwwroot/admin-web/styles.js"&gt;&lt;/script&gt;&lt;script src="/wwwroot/admin-web/vendor.js"&gt;&lt;/script&gt;&lt;script src="/wwwroot/admin-web/main.js"&gt;&lt;/script&gt;&lt;/body&gt;&lt;/html&gt;'@$testhtml -match '(?s)(?&lt;=&lt;body&gt;).*?(?=&lt;\/body&gt;)';$matches[0] $testhtml -match '(?s)(&lt;body&gt;).*?(&lt;\/body&gt;)';$matches[0] </code></pre>
                          </li>
                          <li>The command can also be written:
                            <div style="margin-left: 2em">
                              <pre class="page"><code>[regex]::matches($testhtml,'(?s)(?&lt;=&lt;body&gt;).*?(?=&lt;\/body&gt;)').Value  [regex]::matches($testhtml,'(?s)(&lt;body&gt;).*?(&lt;\/body&gt;)').Value</code></pre>
                            </div>
                          </li>
                          <li>Three different commands to work on a local file. Output does not include body tags:
                            <ol>
                              <li>
                                <pre class="page"><code>(gc -Raw test.html) -match '(?s)(?&lt;=&lt;body&gt;).*?(?=&lt;\/body&gt;)';$matches[0]     [Regex]::Matches((gc -Raw test.html), '(?s)(?&lt;=&lt;body&gt;).*?(?=&lt;\/body&gt;)').Value    gc test.html -Raw | Select-String '(?s)(?&lt;=&lt;body&gt;).*?(?=&lt;\/body&gt;)' -AllMatches | % { $_.Matches } | % { $_.Value }</code></pre>
                                <p>&nbsp;</p>
                              </li>
                            </ol>
                          </li>
                          <li>Output to results.html:
                            <ol>
                              <li>
                                <pre class="page"><code>gc test.html -Raw | Select-String '(?s)(?&lt;=&lt;body&gt;).*?(?=&lt;\/body&gt;)' -AllMatches | % { $_.Matches } | % { $_.Value } | sc results.html </code></pre>
                                <p>&nbsp;</p>
                              </li>
                            </ol>
                          </li>
                          <li>Remote url without and with body tag:
                            <ol>
                              <li>
                                <pre class="page"><code>$testhtml = Invoke-WebRequest -Uri http://www.pgatour.com  <br>$testhtml -match '(?s)(?&lt;=&lt;body&gt;).*?(?=&lt;\/body&gt;)'  <br>$matches[0] <br>$testhtml -match '(?s)(&lt;body&gt;).*?(&lt;\/body&gt;)'  <br>$matches[0]</code></pre>
                              </li>
                            </ol>
                          </li>
                          <li>Remote url without and with body tag. Output to results.html:
                            <ol>
                              <li>
                                <pre class="page"><code>$testhtml = Invoke-WebRequest -Uri http://www.pgatour.com  <br>$testhtml -match '(?s)(?&lt;=&lt;body&gt;).*?(?=&lt;\/body&gt;)'  <br>$matches[0] | sc results.html  </code><br><br><code>$testhtml -match '(?s)(&lt;body&gt;).*?(&lt;\/body&gt;)'  <br>$matches[0] | sc results.html</code></pre>
                                <p>&nbsp;</p>
                              </li>
                            </ol>
                          </li>
                          <li>Remote url between any tag and the first instance of /tag
                            <ol>
                              <li>Never use (.*?|\n)*, always use (?s).*? – <a href="https://stackoverflow.com/users/3832970/wiktor-stribi%c5%bcew">@Wik</a> stackoverflow
                              </li>
                              <li>See <a href="https://stackoverflow.com/a/60566570/8826818">stackoverflow</a>
                              </li>
                              <li>
                                <pre class="page"><code>$testhtml = Invoke-WebRequest -Uri http://www.pgatour.com  <br>$testhtml -match '(&lt;div class="success-message"&gt;)(?s).*?(&lt;\/div&gt;)'  <br>$matches[0]  </code>  <br><br><code>Invoke-WebRequest -Uri http://www.pgatour.com | sc results.html  <br>(gc -raw results.html) -match '(&lt;div class="success-message"&gt;)(?s).*?(&lt;\/div&gt;)'<br>$matches[0]</code></pre>
                              </li>
                            </ol>
                          </li>
                          <li>Remote url by classname. These work but are not very productive. See <a href="http://woshub.com/parsing-html-webpages-with-powershell/" rel="nofollow noreferrer">Parsing HTML Webpages with Powershell.</a>
                            <ol>
                              <li>
                                <pre class="page"><code>$response = Invoke-WebRequest -Uri http://www.pgatour.com  <br>$response.ParsedHtml.body.getElementsByClassName('success-message')  <br>$( $response.ParsedHtml.getElementsByTagName('div') | ?{$_.className -eq 'success-message'} ).outerHTML<br>$( $response.ParsedHtml.body.getElementsByTagName('div') | Where {$_.getAttributeNode('class'). </code></pre>
                              </li>
                            </ol>
                          </li>
                        </ol>
                      </li>
                    </ol>
                  </details>
                </li>
                <li style="text-transform: none">
                  <details>
                    <summary>
                      How to get a YouTube playlistId using Windows 10, PowerShell 5.1 or 7.0, invoke-restmethod and a regular expression for use in youtube-dl? See %windows2%\_27.ps1
                    </summary>
                    <ol>
                      <li>Get YouTube channel NFL &quot;Game Highlights (Week X)&quot; playlistId:
                        <ol>
                          <li>
                            <pre class="page"><code>Game Highlights (Week 4) | NFL 2020</code></pre>is the most unique pattern in the <a href="https://www.youtube.com/c/NFL/playlists">source</a>. Of 256k characters it only occurs once. The playlistId occurs after <b>list=</b> and before <b>&quot;,&quot;webpagetype</b>
                            <pre class="page"><code>&quot;runs&quot;:[{&quot;text&quot;:&quot;Baldy Breakdowns | NFL&quot;,&quot;navigationEndpoint&quot;:{&quot;clickTrackingParams&quot;:&quot;CEAQljUYACITCLnRyYi8oewCFTDDFgkdFiYOzTIJYzQtdmlkZW9zWhhVQ0RWWVE0WmhibTNTMmRsejdQMUdCRGc=&quot;,&quot;commandMetadata&quot;:{&quot;webCommandMetadata&quot;:{&quot;url&quot;:&quot;/watch?v=z5xm1yUnF_A\u0026list=PLRdw3IjKY2gkxzCrNTjJ64jnCc6ZLjkg4&quot;,&quot;webPageType&quot;:&quot;WEB_PAGE_TYPE_WATCH&quot;,&quot;rootVe&quot;:3832}},}}]&quot;runs&quot;:[{&quot;text&quot;:&quot;Game Highlights (Week 4) | NFL 2020&quot;,&quot;navigationEndpoint&quot;:{&quot;clickTrackingParams&quot;:&quot;CDUQljUYDyITCKnihZHZnuwCFdXhggodkEkDEzIJYzQtdmlkZW9zWhhVQ0RWWVE0WmhibTNTMmRsejdQMUdCRGc=&quot;,&quot;commandMetadata&quot;:{&quot;webCommandMetadata&quot;:{&quot;url&quot;:&quot;/watch?v=qAZj4vQRleo\u0026</code></pre>
                            <h4><code>list=</code></h4>
                            <pre><span class="hljs-code">PLRdw3IjKY2gmo2FVKs1NlGtfQX6FB_JkE</span></pre>
                            <h4><code>&quot;,&quot;webPageType</code></h4>
                            <pre>&quot;:&quot;WEB_PAGE_TYPE_WATCH&quot;,&quot;rootVe&quot;:3832}},}}]</pre><code><a href="https://www.bing.com/search?&amp;q=nfl+2020+schedule">https://www.bing.com/search?&amp;q=nfl+2020+schedule</a><br>
                            <br></code>
                            <pre class="page"><code><code># BEGIN Get the YouTube channel NFL "Game Highlights (Week X)" playlistId with $env:windows2\_27.ps1# Get the start date of the NFL season into a text file so you can use the text file to determine the week of the season next week.if(!(Test-Path $env:windows2\_27.ps1NFLstart.txt)) {$zyear=get-date -Format "yyyy"start "https://www.bing.com/search?&q=NFL+$zyear+schedule"$zstart=Read-Host -Prompt 'Go to the browser, get the start date of the NFL season, close the browser and enter the start date into this window (mm/dd/yy i.e. 09/10/20) 'if ($zstart) {$zstart|out-file $env:windows2\_27.ps1NFLstart.txtWrite-output "The start date of the NFL season in mm/dd/yy format. See _27.ps1" | add-content $env:windows2\_27.ps1NFLstart.txt} else {Write-Host "You must enter the start date.  Script will exit in 60 seconds."start-sleep 60exit }}$zyear=get-date -Format "yyyy"$zstart=gc $env:windows2\_27.ps1NFLstart.txt -first 1 ; # load start date into memory$zweek=New-TimeSpan -Start $zstart -End (get-date -format MM/dd/yy) ; # how many days have passed since the season began?# $zweek.days / 7 ; # Display how many weeks have passed since the season began.if(($zweek.days / 7) -match '\.'){$zweek=[math]::ceiling($zweek.days / 7)}else{$zweek=($zweek.days / 7 + 1)} ; # If $zweek has a decimal round $zweek up even if the fraction is &lt; .5    If it is an integer add one to it.$zweek=[int]$zweek ; # The week of the season as an integer.# $zweek ; # Display the week of the season.if ($z0 -eq "Fri" -or $z0 -eq "Mon" -or $z0 -eq "Tue"){$z=Invoke-restmethod https://www.youtube.com/c/NFL/playlists; # If it is Fri or Mon or Tue load the youtube page containing the playlistId into memory.$z=$z -replace "[^a-zA-Z0-9_-]" ; # Strip out all non-word characters except underscore and hyphen$z -match "(?s)GameHighlightsWeek$zweekNFL$zyear.*?list(.*?)webPageType" | out-null ; # Match the playlistId with a regular expression. The Id is captured by (.*?). See Explanation of the regular expression by Regex Buddy below.$zid=$matches[1]; # The playlistIdWrite-host "$zid is the playlistId of the playlist `"Game Highlights Week ($zweek) NFL | $zyear`""; # Display the playlistId#pushd "$env:userprofile\downloads\_1nfl" # Change to directory $env:userprofile\downloads\_1nfl$host.ui.rawui.WindowTitle = "This is _27.ps1. First $z0 $zid" #powershell window title for first pass# youtube-dl --download-archive $env:temp2\archive.txt --playlist-items 1-16 $zidyoutube-dl --download-archive $env:temp2\archive.txt "$zid" # Download all the videos in the playlist (~15)$host.ui.rawui.WindowTitle = "This is _27.ps1. Second $z0 $zid" #powershell window title for second passwhile (test-path *.part){# youtube-dl --download-archive $env:temp2\archive.txt --playlist-items 1-16 $zidyoutube-dl --download-archive $env:temp2\archive.txt "$zid" # While loop to restart download at point where download failed until download successful.popd # Return to directory before pushd}}##    END Get the YouTube channel NFL "Game Highlights (Week X)" playlistId</code></code></pre>
                            <p>Work local:</p><!-- changed < to &lt; and & to &amp; in the following <pre class=page><code> ... </code></pre>-->
                            <pre class="page"><code>$html = @'&lt;!doctype html&gt;&lt;html  style=&quot;font-size: 10px;font-family: Roboto, Arial, sans-serif;&quot; lang=&quot;en-US&quot; dir=&quot;ltr&quot; gl=&quot;US&quot;&gt;&lt;head&gt;{&quot;runs&quot;:[{&quot;text&quot;:&quot;Can't-Miss Plays (Week 4) | NFL 2020&quot;,&quot;navigationEndpoint&quot;:{&quot;clickTrackingParams&quot;:&quot;CEQQljUYACITCKnihZHZnuwCFdXhggodkEkDEzIJYzQtdmlkZW9zWhhVQ0RWWVE0WmhibTNTMmRsejdQMUdCRGc=&quot;,&quot;commandMetadata&quot;:{&quot;webCommandMetadata&quot;:{&quot;url&quot;:&quot;/watch?v=359dcOIvOZ0\u0026list=PLRdw3IjKY2gn8JlCazlMFvhxDp0QIbrFY&quot;,&quot;webPageType&quot;:&quot;WEB_PAGE_TYPE_WATCH&quot;,&quot;rootVe&quot;:3832}},&quot;watchEndpoint&quot;:{&quot;videoId&quot;:&quot;359dcOIvOZ0&quot;,&quot;playlistId&quot;:&quot;PLRdw3IjKY2gn8JlCazlMFvhxDp0QIbrFY&quot;,&quot;params&quot;:&quot;OAI%3D&quot;}}}]}{&quot;runs&quot;:[{&quot;text&quot;:&quot;Game Highlights (Week 4) | NFL 2020&quot;,&quot;navigationEndpoint&quot;:{&quot;clickTrackingParams&quot;:&quot;CDUQljUYDyITCKnihZHZnuwCFdXhggodkEkDEzIJYzQtdmlkZW9zWhhVQ0RWWVE0WmhibTNTMmRsejdQMUdCRGc=&quot;,&quot;commandMetadata&quot;:{&quot;webCommandMetadata&quot;:{&quot;url&quot;:&quot;/watch?v=qAZj4vQRleo\u0026list=PLRdw3IjKY2gmo2FVKs1NlGtfQX6FB_JkE&quot;,&quot;webPageType&quot;:&quot;WEB_PAGE_TYPE_WATCH&quot;,&quot;rootVe&quot;:3832}},&quot;watchEndpoint&quot;:{&quot;videoId&quot;:&quot;qAZj4vQRleo&quot;,&quot;playlistId&quot;:&quot;PLRdw3IjKY2gmo2FVKs1NlGtfQX6FB_JkE&quot;,&quot;params&quot;:&quot;OAI%3D&quot;}}}]}&lt;/body&gt;&lt;/html&gt;'@$zyear=get-date -Format "yyyy"$zstart=gc $env:windows2\_27.ps1NFLstart.txt -first 1 ; # load start date into memory$zweek=New-TimeSpan -Start $zstart -End (get-date -format MM/dd/yy) ; # how many days have passed since the season began?# $zweek.days / 7 ; # Display how many weeks have passed since the season began.if(($zweek.days / 7) -match '\.'){$zweek=[math]::ceiling($zweek.days / 7)}else{$zweek=($zweek.days / 7 + 1)} ; # If $zweek has a decimal round $zweek up even if the fraction is &lt; .5    If it is an integer add one to it.$zweek=[int]$zweek ; # The week of the season as an integer.# $zweek ; # Display the week of the season.if ($z0 -eq "Fri" -or $z0 -eq "Mon" -or $z0 -eq "Tue"){$z=Invoke-restmethod https://www.youtube.com/c/NFL/playlists; # If it is Fri or Mon or Tue load remote NFL source file into memory.$z=$z -replace "[^a-zA-Z0-9_-]" ; # Strip out all non-word characters except underscore and hyphen$z -match "(?s)GameHighlightsWeek$zweekNFL$zyear.*?list(.*?)webPageType" | out-null ; # Match the playlistId with a regular expression. The Id is captured by (.*?)$zid=$matches[1]; # The playlistIdWrite-host "$zid is the playlistId of the playlist `"Game Highlights Week ($zweek) NFL | $zyear`""; # Display the playlistId#</code></pre>
