                    <ol>
                      <li id="#write-a-new-creationtime">Creationtime: write a new creationtime
                        <p style="padding:14px 0 0 0">Powershell default file sort is oldest files first:</p>
                        <blockquote>
                          <pre class="page"><code>gci -file | Sort-Object creationtime | select name,creationtime</code></pre>
                        </blockquote>
                        <p>Sort by newest file</p>
                        <blockquote>
                          <pre class="page"><code>gci -file | sort -desc creationtime | select name,creationtime</code></pre>
                        </blockquote>
                        <p>Write new creationtime. Each file is one minute newer. Force causes gci to include hidden files.</p>
                        <pre class="page"><code>$z=get-date$arr = @(gci -force | Sort-Object creationtime)$arr | ForEach {$_.CreationTime  = $z$z = $z.addMinutes(-1)}</code></pre>
